# editors use the modern React hooks pattern from reactor-browser

Document editors follow a consistent pattern using auto-generated hooks from `@powerhousedao/reactor-browser`:

```typescript
import { generateId } from "document-model/core";
import { useSelectedTodoDocument } from "../hooks/useTodoDocument.js";
import { addTodo } from "../../document-models/todo/gen/creators.js";

export default function Editor() {
  const [document, dispatch] = useSelectedTodoDocument();

  function handleAddTodo(values: { title: string }) {
    if (values.title) {
      dispatch(addTodo({ id: generateId(), title: values.title }));
    }
  }
}
```

Key points:
- `useSelectedXDocument` is auto-generated per document model — since [[useSelectedDocument hook is auto-generated per document model]], never implement it manually
- Since [[editors import action creators from gen/creators not from model source]], the import path is `../../document-models/<model>/gen/creators.js`
- Since [[generateId from document-model/core provides deterministic IDs for dispatch]], IDs are created before dispatch, not inside reducers

